prediction of MACE-3M, the sensitivity and specificity were 83.3% and 82.7% for a Plt-GGT value >265 mU/mg, 74.7% and 63.3% for an LVEF >45, and 86.7% and 77.3% for a TIMI Risk Score>4, respectively.
After multiple regression analysis, Plt-GGT >265 mU/mg, length of hospitalization >5 days, TIMI risk score >4, and family history of CAD were found to be independent predictors of MACE-3M with a positive predictive value of 65.8%, 61.9%, 60.5%, and 43% and negative predictive value of 92.5%, 94%, 93.5%, and 83.9%, respectively. We found that the risk of MACE-3M is 4.8 times higher in patients having a

